PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775488261
OL,3,CArtemis II approaching far-side of
OL,4,Cmoon never seen before by naked eye
OL,6,FIt will take the crew four days to
OL,7,Fthen get back to Earth, with a
OL,8,Fsplashdown in the Pacific concluding
OL,9,Ftheir test flight on Friday.
OL,11,FDuring their fly-around, the
OL,12,Fastronauts will pass as close as 4,070
OL,13,Fmiles (6,550 kilometres) to the moon.
OL,15,FTheir moon mentor, Nasa geologist
OL,16,FKelsey Young, expects thousands of
OL,17,Fpictures to be taken.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
