PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775488261
OL,3,CArtemis II approaching far-side of
OL,4,Cmoon never seen before by naked eye
OL,6,F"People all over the world connect
OL,7,Fwith the moon. This is something that
OL,8,Fevery single person on this planet can
OL,9,Funderstand and connect with," Young
OL,10,Fsaid on the eve of the flyby.
OL,12,FArtemis II is Nasa's first astronaut
OL,13,Fmoonshot since Apollo 17 in 1972 and
OL,14,Fsets the stage for next year's Artemis
OL,15,FIII, which will see another Orion crew
OL,16,Fpractice docking with lunar landers in
OL,17,Forbit around Earth.
OL,19,FThe culminating moon landing by two
OL,20,Fastronauts near the moon's south pole
OL,21,Fwill follow on Artemis IV in 2028.
